# UX/UI Improvement Plan — iskrib_v3

## Context
The app has a polished editorial aesthetic (glass morphism, amber/sage accents, Playfair Display + Lora typography) but several UX gaps: silent mutation failures, no feed skeletons, no page transitions, inconsistent spacing tokens, and partial accessibility. This plan addresses four areas in priority order.

---

## Phase 1: Foundation — Design Tokens + Toast System

### 1A. Design Tokens
**File:** `client/src/index.css` — add to `:root` (and mirror in `[data-theme="dark"]` where needed)

```css
/* Spacing (4px grid) */
--space-1: 4px;  --space-2: 8px;  --space-3: 12px;
--space-4: 16px; --space-6: 24px; --space-8: 32px;
--space-10: 40px; --space-12: 48px; --space-16: 64px;

/* Type scale */
--text-xs: 0.7rem;     --text-sm: 0.78rem;
--text-base: 0.875rem;  --text-md: 1rem;
--text-lg: 1.125rem;    --text-xl: 1.5rem;
--text-2xl: 2rem;       --text-3xl: 2.5rem;

/* Animation */
--ease-out-quart: cubic-bezier(0.25, 1, 0.5, 1);
--ease-spring: cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1);
--duration-fast: 150ms;
--duration-normal: 250ms;
--duration-slow: 400ms;

/* Focus */
--focus-ring: 0 0 0 2px var(--bg-primary), 0 0 0 4px var(--accent-amber);
```

### 1B. Global Toast System
**New files:**
- `client/src/components/Toast/ToastContext.jsx` — Context + Provider + `useToast()` hook
- `client/src/components/Toast/Toast.jsx` — Individual toast (Framer Motion enter/exit)
- `client/src/components/Toast/ToastContainer.jsx` — Portal wrapper, stacks max 3 toasts
- `client/src/components/Toast/Toast.css` — Glass morphism styling, left accent stripe per type

**API:**
```jsx
const { toast } = useToast();
toast.success('Post bookmarked');
toast.error('Failed to save. Please try again.');
toast.warning('You are offline');
toast.info('Draft auto-saved');
```

**Design:** Bottom-right on desktop, bottom-center on mobile. Glass morphism bg, left color stripe (success=green, error=red, warning=amber, info=purple). Auto-dismiss: 3.5s success/info, 5s error/warning.

**Integration — modify:**
- `client/src/main.jsx` — wrap with `<ToastProvider>` inside `ThemeProvider`
- `client/src/components/HomePage/postCards/PostCards.jsx` — replace ad-hoc `bookmarkedMessage`/`repostToastMessage` state with `toast.success()`. Add `onError` callbacks to mutation `.mutate()` calls.
- `client/src/components/HomePage/ContentViewer/ContentView.jsx` — same: replace inline bookmark toast, add error toasts to reaction/follow/bookmark mutations
- `client/src/components/comments/comments.jsx` — replace `throw new Error` in catch block with `toast.error('Failed to post comment')`
- `client/src/components/HomePage/Editor/Editor.jsx` — add error toast for publish/save failures
- `client/src/components/RepostModal/RepostModal.jsx` — use toast for repost confirmation

**Pattern:** Error handling at call sites via `mutate({...}, { onError: () => toast.error('...') })`, NOT inside shared hooks.

---

## Phase 2: Feed & Page Polish

### 2A. Feed Skeleton Loaders
**New files:**
- `client/src/components/Skeletons/FeedCardSkeleton.jsx` + `FeedCardSkeleton.css`

Reuse shimmer `@keyframes` from `client/src/components/Discovery/RelatedPosts.css` (`rp-shimmer`). Skeleton mimics PostCard layout: avatar circle, name/date bars, title bar, two text bars, action icons row. Render 4 skeletons when `isFeedLoading`.

**Modify:** `PostCards.jsx` — replace `MoonLoader` with `<FeedCardSkeleton count={4} />`

### 2B. Empty States
**New files:**
- `client/src/components/EmptyState/EmptyState.jsx` + `EmptyState.css`

Reusable: `<EmptyState icon={} title="" description="" action={{ label, onClick }} />`

**Integrate into:** `PostCards.jsx` (empty feed), Bookmarks (no bookmarks), search (no results)

### 2C. Reading Progress Bar
**New files:**
- `client/src/components/ReadingProgress/ReadingProgress.jsx` + `ReadingProgress.css`

Thin fixed bar at viewport top, amber gradient fill, tracks scroll through article via `requestAnimationFrame`.

**Modify:** `ContentView.jsx` — render `<ReadingProgress />` scoped to article content

### 2D. Page Transitions
**Modify:** `client/src/components/HomePage/Home.jsx` (line 328)

Wrap `<Outlet>` with `AnimatePresence mode="wait"` + `motion.div`:
```jsx
<AnimatePresence mode="wait">
    <motion.div
        key={location.pathname}
        initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }}
        animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
        exit={{ opacity: 0 }}
        transition={{ duration: 0.2, ease: [0.25, 1, 0.5, 1] }}
    >
        <Outlet context={{ clickOpenSidebar: handleClickMobileProfileLink, handleOpenTextEditor }} />
    </motion.div>
</AnimatePresence>
```

Sidebar stays mounted — only content area transitions. `useLocation()` already imported.

---

## Phase 3: Micro-interactions & Animations

### 3A. Button Press Feedback (Global)
**Modify:** `client/src/index.css` — add utility:
```css
.pressable { transition: transform var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-out-quart); }
.pressable:active { transform: scale(0.97); }
```
Apply `.pressable` to key buttons in PostCards, ContentView, Sidebar.

### 3B. Like/Reaction Pop
**Modify:** `client/src/components/Reactions/reactions.css` — add:
```css
@keyframes reaction-pop {
    0% { transform: scale(1); }
    50% { transform: scale(1.25); }
    100% { transform: scale(1); }
}
.reaction-button.just-reacted { animation: reaction-pop 300ms var(--ease-spring); }
```
**Modify:** `ReactionButton.jsx` — briefly toggle `just-reacted` class on click via state

### 3C. Bookmark Bounce
**Modify:** `postcards.css` — add:
```css
@keyframes bookmark-bounce {
    0% { transform: scale(1); }
    30% { transform: scale(0.85); }
    60% { transform: scale(1.2); }
    100% { transform: scale(1); }
}
```
**Modify:** `PostCards.jsx` — add conditional class on bookmark button when toggled

### 3D. Feed Cards Staggered Entrance
**Modify:** `PostCards.jsx` — wrap each card in `motion.div` with:
```jsx
initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 16 }}
animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
transition={{ duration: 0.35, delay: index * 0.05, ease: [0.25, 0.46, 0.45, 0.94] }}
```
Only stagger first page (check `pageIndex === 0`); subsequent pages animate without delay.

### 3E. Follow Button + Comment Slide-In
- Follow button: add `transition` + `:active scale(0.95)` in `contentviewer.css`
- New comments: wrap optimistic comments in `motion.div` with `initial={{ opacity: 0, x: -20 }}` in `comments.jsx`

---

## Phase 4: Accessibility

### 4A. Focus Rings
**Modify:** `client/src/index.css` — add:
```css
:focus-visible { outline: none; box-shadow: var(--focus-ring); border-radius: 4px; }
:focus:not(:focus-visible) { outline: none; box-shadow: none; }
```

### 4B. Reduced Motion
**Modify:** `client/src/index.css` — add:
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    *, *::before, *::after {
        animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
        animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
        transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    }
}
```
For Framer Motion: use `useReducedMotion()` from framer-motion in key animated components to conditionally disable.

### 4C. Skip-to-Content
**Modify:** `App.jsx` — add `<a href="#main-content" className="skip-to-content">` as first child
**Modify:** `Home.jsx` — add `id="main-content"` to `.center-bar-holder-container`
**Modify:** `index.css` — off-screen by default, visible on `:focus`

### 4D. Aria Labels (Bulk Pass)
**Modify:**
- `PostCards.jsx` — `aria-label` on like/comment/bookmark/repost/share buttons, `role="article"` on cards
- `ReactionButton.jsx` — `aria-label="React"`, `aria-pressed` attribute
- `comments.jsx` — `aria-label` on close/submit buttons
- `Sidebar.jsx` — `role="navigation"`, `aria-label="Main navigation"`
- `ContentView.jsx` — `role="article"`, labels on all action buttons

### 4E. Focus Trap for Modals
**New file:** `client/src/utils/useFocusTrap.js`
Traps Tab/Shift+Tab within container, restores focus on unmount.

**Apply to:** AuthModal, RepostModal, CommentsModal, Editor

---

## Build Order (by impact-to-effort)

| Step | What | Why first |
|------|------|-----------|
| 1 | Design tokens (1A) | Foundation for everything else |
| 2 | Toast system (1B) | Highest-impact single change — fixes silent failures |
| 3 | Feed skeletons (2A) | Huge perceived perf improvement, low effort |
| 4 | Focus rings + reduced motion (4A, 4B) | Small CSS additions, big a11y win |
| 5 | Page transitions (2D) | Makes navigation feel premium |
| 6 | Micro-interactions (3A-3E) | Polish layer across the app |
| 7 | Empty states (2B) + Reading progress (2C) | Nice-to-haves with moderate impact |
| 8 | Skip-to-content + aria labels + focus trap (4C-4E) | Accessibility completeness |

## Verification
- Toast: trigger error by disconnecting network, verify red toast appears + auto-dismisses
- Skeletons: throttle network in DevTools, confirm shimmer cards show on feed load
- Page transitions: navigate between feed/bookmarks/notifications, confirm smooth fade
- Focus rings: Tab through the app, verify amber outline on all interactive elements
- Reduced motion: enable in OS settings, confirm no animations play
- Micro-interactions: like/bookmark posts, confirm pop/bounce animations
- Empty states: view empty bookmarks page, confirm illustration + CTA renders

